    "Finally, as in the previous example, we can also start from the statement of Theorem 2.1: with probability at least 1 -δ,",
    "and restrict here ρ to the set of Gaussian distributions N (m, s 2 I d).",
    "This leads to the definition of a new data-dependent probability measure, ρλ = N (m, s2 I d) where (m, s) = argmin",
    "when this is well defined (we can adapt the definition of ρλ to the situation when there is no minimum, we postpone this to the next paragraph).",
    "While the Gibbs posterior ρλ can be quite a complicated object, one simply has to solve this minimization problem to get ρλ."
